# Peaky Ledger — Windsurf Rules

## Project Context

Read `CODEBASE.md` in the project root for complete architecture, schema, and conventions.

## Quick Facts

| Key | Value |
|---|---|
| Framework | Next.js 16.2.7 (App Router) — **breaking changes from older versions** |
| UI | React 19.2.4 |
| Language | TypeScript 5 (strict) |
| Database | Supabase (Postgres + Auth + Storage + RLS) |
| State | Zustand 5 (persisted) |
| Styling | Vanilla CSS with HSL design tokens — **NO TAILWIND** |
| Path Alias | `@/*` → `./src/*` |

## Architecture Rules

1. All pages in `src/app/(journal)/` are `'use client'` components
2. All DB queries go through `src/utils/supabase/queries.ts`
3. Browser Supabase client: `src/utils/supabase/client.ts`
4. Server Supabase client: `src/utils/supabase/server.ts`
5. Middleware is `src/proxy.ts` (not `middleware.ts`)
6. Types centralized in `src/types/journal.ts`
7. Single Zustand store in `src/store/useJournalStore.ts`
8. CSS in `src/app/globals.css` — use CSS custom properties, not hardcoded values
9. Broker integrations implement `BrokerAdapter` interface from `src/utils/broker/adapter.ts`
10. API routes under `src/app/api/broker/` handle server-side broker operations

## Forbidden Patterns

- Tailwind CSS or any CSS framework
- CSS modules
- Direct `@supabase/supabase-js` imports (use wrappers)
- `getServerSideProps` / `getStaticProps` (App Router only)
- Hardcoded color values (use CSS custom properties)
- Database queries outside of `queries.ts`
- New middleware files (extend `proxy.ts`)

